            "type": "text",
            "text": "Query Engines vs Retrievers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LlamaIndex separates retrieval from generation into two layers:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Retriever:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Takes a query string, returns a ranked list of "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "NodeWithScore",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " objects. No LLM involved."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Query engine:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Takes a query string, runs the retriever, passes the nodes to an LLM, and returns a "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Response",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " object containing the answer and source nodes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You can use a retriever standalone for inspection, testing, or when you want to implement your own generation logic. Use a query engine when you want the full RAG pipeline in one call."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Retriever only (no LLM)\nretriever = index.as_retriever(similarity_top_k=5)\nnodes = retriever.retrieve(\"What was Q3 revenue?\")\nfor node in nodes:\n    print(node.score, node.text[:100])\n\n# Query engine (retrieve + generate)\nquery_engine = index.as_query_engine()\nresponse = query_engine.query(\"What was Q3 revenue?\")\nprint(response)                  # the generated answer\nprint(response.source_nodes)     # which nodes were used"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "A query engine is a retriever + a response synthesiser. Understanding each piece separately makes debugging much easier."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
